1
00:00:18,220 --> 00:00:24,540
♪The moon sinks, ripples dance,
violet stars awaken♪

2
00:00:25,220 --> 00:00:28,780
♪As time dissolves without a trace♪

3
00:00:29,540 --> 00:00:35,860
♪Frosted memories scatter;
silk cannot veil the past♪

4
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:41,300
♪Fate is drifting in silence♪

5
00:00:42,580 --> 00:00:47,460
♪Let winds and sands
accompany the road ahead♪

6
00:00:48,020 --> 00:00:52,860
♪Looking back, joys and sorrows linger,
no regrets remain♪

7
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:58,500
♪Breaking free
from the depths of darkness♪

8
00:00:59,620 --> 00:01:03,940
♪Like pearls of tears,
we swirl with fate's embrace♪

9
00:01:23,780 --> 00:01:26,780
[Adapted from "The Legend
of Kunshan Jade" by Tan Tianyin]

10
00:01:26,780 --> 00:01:29,740
[The Story of Pearl Girl]

11
00:01:30,380 --> 00:01:32,980
[Episode 2]

12
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:00,890
Not bad at all.

13
00:03:19,620 --> 00:03:21,840
In the rising tower,
jade pendants sway in the breeze,

14
00:03:23,060 --> 00:03:24,470
while pearls glisten

15
00:03:25,310 --> 00:03:26,700
under the stars.

16
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:18,100
Wonderful!

17
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:19,500
Bravo!

18
00:04:27,470 --> 00:04:28,990
Presenting today's highlight:

19
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:31,660
a blood-stained Tridacna pearl.

20
00:04:32,150 --> 00:04:33,190
It wards off all evil

21
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:34,340
and weighs five maces.

22
00:04:35,190 --> 00:04:36,590
Its starting bid is three million maces.

23
00:04:37,270 --> 00:04:39,500
Tridacna pearls are precious.

24
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,500
What does she mean by "blood-stained"?

25
00:04:42,060 --> 00:04:43,190
This pearl hostess

26
00:04:43,190 --> 00:04:45,430
speaks not a word of truth.

27
00:04:46,220 --> 00:04:47,430
Pearl hunting is tough,

28
00:04:48,030 --> 00:04:49,870
and so is selling them.

29
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:52,940
Mr. Zhang, you're truly a kind soul.

30
00:04:58,060 --> 00:05:00,750
Mr. Peng, with your confidence
and grandeur,

31
00:05:00,750 --> 00:05:03,030
this treasure should go to you.

32
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:05,780
Mr. Peng, are you interested in bidding?

33
00:05:05,780 --> 00:05:08,030
A blood-stained Tridacna pearl
is indeed rare.

34
00:05:08,030 --> 00:05:10,340
I'll offer two million maces.

35
00:05:10,340 --> 00:05:12,310
The starting bid is three million maces.

36
00:05:12,310 --> 00:05:14,660
Surely you jest, Mr. Peng.

37
00:05:15,380 --> 00:05:15,910
Steward Cui,

38
00:05:15,910 --> 00:05:17,270
what Mr. Peng means

39
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:19,220
is that this pearl is flawless,

40
00:05:19,220 --> 00:05:21,060
and he's willing to raise the bid
by two million.

41
00:05:22,310 --> 00:05:23,380
Isn't that right, Mr. Peng?

42
00:05:23,380 --> 00:05:24,620
I see.

43
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:27,100
Thank you, Mr. Peng.

44
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,100
Thank you, Master Yan.

45
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:34,540
However, this pearl isn't flawless.

46
00:05:35,380 --> 00:05:36,660
Are you talking down your own item?

47
00:05:36,660 --> 00:05:38,270
It has an extraordinary flaw,

48
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:39,430
the blood from a living person.

49
00:05:39,820 --> 00:05:41,820
I obtained this pearl myself,

50
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:44,750
and the wound from gathering it
won't heal.

51
00:05:45,540 --> 00:05:47,070
As I said,

52
00:05:48,340 --> 00:05:49,710
a Tridacna pearl, tainted with blood,

53
00:05:50,180 --> 00:05:51,630
wards off all evil.

54
00:05:52,340 --> 00:05:54,100
That's what makes
this pearl so precious.

55
00:05:54,100 --> 00:05:55,910
Tridacna pearls are rare for sure,

56
00:05:55,910 --> 00:05:57,710
but can they really ward off evil
after being tainted with blood?

57
00:05:57,710 --> 00:05:58,540
Exactly.

58
00:05:58,540 --> 00:05:59,150
It sounds made up.

59
00:05:59,150 --> 00:06:00,070
I've brought you here

60
00:06:00,070 --> 00:06:01,710
to see this pearl auction as promised.

61
00:06:01,710 --> 00:06:03,100
Now, about our wager...

62
00:06:04,220 --> 00:06:06,950
I was indeed overconfident.

63
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:09,950
Mr. Zhang, you're truly
a man of your word.

64
00:06:11,590 --> 00:06:14,220
I'm not really keen on this pearl,

65
00:06:15,220 --> 00:06:16,340
but this box

66
00:06:17,540 --> 00:06:20,390
isn't something ordinary folks own.

67
00:06:20,390 --> 00:06:21,150
Thanks a lot.

68
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:25,540
Since you're so gracious,

69
00:06:25,980 --> 00:06:26,740
in return,

70
00:06:27,830 --> 00:06:29,710
I'll help you lend a hand
to that pearl hostess.

71
00:06:31,030 --> 00:06:33,180
The Tridacna pearl is one
of the seven treasures of Buddhism.

72
00:06:33,540 --> 00:06:35,660
An ordinary Tridacna pearl is ominous.

73
00:06:36,100 --> 00:06:37,270
Gathering it brings misfortune.

74
00:06:37,780 --> 00:06:39,340
But if it bears human blood,

75
00:06:39,830 --> 00:06:41,540
it gains the power to ward off evil

76
00:06:41,540 --> 00:06:43,070
and can truly be called
a talisman pearl.

77
00:06:43,470 --> 00:06:44,860
I am willing to bid

78
00:06:46,070 --> 00:06:46,890
six million maces.

79
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:48,420
Six million maces?

80
00:06:48,830 --> 00:06:50,830
However rare it is,
it can't be worth that much.

81
00:06:50,830 --> 00:06:51,660
Exactly.

82
00:06:51,660 --> 00:06:53,180
No one's ever bid this high before.

83
00:06:53,180 --> 00:06:53,980
What,

84
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:55,340
can it really ward off evil?

85
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:57,350
Can it really repel all harm?

86
00:06:57,350 --> 00:06:58,310
- Can it?
- Really?

87
00:07:00,190 --> 00:07:01,990
Even if it could,
it's still not worth six million maces.

88
00:07:19,150 --> 00:07:20,710
Take the offer while you can.

89
00:07:26,270 --> 00:07:27,470
Thank you for your kindness, sir.

90
00:07:30,100 --> 00:07:31,180
But I'm wagering my life here,

91
00:07:33,280 --> 00:07:34,590
not just a pearl.

92
00:07:48,420 --> 00:07:49,710
Only six million maces?

93
00:07:51,590 --> 00:07:53,030
Master Yan, such a price hardly honors

94
00:07:53,030 --> 00:07:55,180
this one-of-a-kind treasure,

95
00:07:55,180 --> 00:07:56,300
the Mermaid's Tear.

96
00:07:57,470 --> 00:07:58,470
Steward Cui,

97
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:01,660
this pearl hostess of yours
is full of lies.

98
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:03,150
One moment it's a talisman pearl,

99
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,910
and now it becomes the Mermaid's Tear?

100
00:08:06,070 --> 00:08:07,660
In "In Search of the Supernatural,"

101
00:08:08,030 --> 00:08:09,980
it's said there are merfolk
beyond the South Sea,

102
00:08:10,740 --> 00:08:11,860
living like fish in the water

103
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:13,030
and weaving tirelessly.

104
00:08:13,630 --> 00:08:14,780
When they cry,

105
00:08:15,420 --> 00:08:16,710
their tears become pearls.

106
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:25,100
Everyone,

107
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,420
Master Yan is an esteemed guest
from the State of Kang.

108
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:29,630
Since he has bid six million maces,

109
00:08:30,590 --> 00:08:31,590
this pearl should go

110
00:08:31,590 --> 00:08:31,830
to Yan...

111
00:08:31,830 --> 00:08:32,780
Steward Cui!

112
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:35,340
When the mermaid cries,
her tears turn into pearls.

113
00:08:36,630 --> 00:08:39,030
A Mermaid's Tear is worth a life.

114
00:08:51,630 --> 00:08:52,470
Mr. Zhang,

115
00:08:55,710 --> 00:08:57,590
I ask you to appraise it.

116
00:09:01,510 --> 00:09:03,590
Sell it for seven million,
and you're free.

117
00:09:03,950 --> 00:09:05,740
If you fail, you will die.

118
00:09:14,390 --> 00:09:15,980
If this pearl is so precious,

119
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:18,790
then I bid

120
00:09:20,740 --> 00:09:21,950
seven million maces.

121
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:23,980
Seven million?

122
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:27,610
Even if it wards off all evil,
that's too high!

123
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,510
Mr. Zhang,

124
00:09:28,780 --> 00:09:31,710
seven million maces is no small sum.

125
00:09:34,710 --> 00:09:35,630
Thank you, sir!

126
00:09:46,030 --> 00:09:48,830
This pearl, bid at seven million
by Mr. Zhang,

127
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:51,150
now belongs to him!

128
00:10:09,870 --> 00:10:12,580
This gold willow leaf isn't something
an ordinary person can possess.

129
00:10:13,870 --> 00:10:15,300
It seems I was presumptuous.

130
00:10:24,910 --> 00:10:25,870
Steward Cui,

131
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:27,870
I hope

132
00:10:29,110 --> 00:10:30,390
you'll keep your word.

133
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:36,300
Revealing his identity so easily,

134
00:10:36,940 --> 00:10:38,060
he's unfit for bigger responsibilities.

135
00:10:39,820 --> 00:10:41,630
It's precisely his sincerity
and kindness

136
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:42,780
that makes him

137
00:10:43,270 --> 00:10:44,580
trustworthy for this task.

138
00:10:45,030 --> 00:10:46,750
Shall we continue
with the original plan, then?

139
00:10:47,510 --> 00:10:48,150
Yes.

140
00:10:49,870 --> 00:10:50,540
By the way,

141
00:10:52,110 --> 00:10:53,540
just now, I saw a woman

142
00:10:53,990 --> 00:10:55,460
with a scar on her face.

143
00:10:56,300 --> 00:10:57,270
Find her for me.

144
00:10:58,180 --> 00:10:59,110
An old acquaintance?

145
00:11:00,030 --> 00:11:00,660
Yes.

146
00:11:04,940 --> 00:11:05,780
Mr. Zhang.

147
00:11:10,510 --> 00:11:13,420
Greetings, sir.
I'm Duanwu, a pearl diver.

148
00:11:13,420 --> 00:11:14,460
Thank you, sir.

149
00:11:14,460 --> 00:11:15,230
Duanwu?

150
00:11:17,910 --> 00:11:19,270
As in early midsummer.

151
00:11:19,820 --> 00:11:20,940
It's a fine name.

152
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:26,940
In early midsummer,

153
00:11:27,460 --> 00:11:29,390
the Seven Mansions of the Azure Dragon
rise to the southern sky

154
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:31,700
reaching the centermost position.

155
00:11:32,350 --> 00:11:33,630
I didn't know that.

156
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:35,230
Mr. Zhang, I came here

157
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:36,630
to thank you

158
00:11:36,630 --> 00:11:38,060
and express my gratitude.

159
00:11:38,060 --> 00:11:39,630
Your kindness means the world to me.

160
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:42,150
It was just a small gesture.

161
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:43,990
To you, sir,

162
00:11:44,420 --> 00:11:45,540
it may have been,

163
00:11:47,180 --> 00:11:48,270
but to me,

164
00:11:49,510 --> 00:11:50,510
it's of great significance.

165
00:11:51,780 --> 00:11:53,230
Please don't misunderstand me.

166
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:54,940
I only want to say

167
00:11:54,940 --> 00:11:56,870
that if you ever need my help,

168
00:11:56,870 --> 00:11:58,390
I'll be there,

169
00:11:58,390 --> 00:11:59,420
no matter what it takes.

170
00:12:00,990 --> 00:12:03,060
Then I'll look forward
to your assistance someday.

171
00:12:03,630 --> 00:12:04,540
Until we meet again.

172
00:12:04,540 --> 00:12:05,510
Until we meet again.

173
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:13,540
By the way,

174
00:12:18,350 --> 00:12:19,510
this is actually my first time here.

175
00:12:20,780 --> 00:12:23,420
Would you mind showing me around Hepu?

176
00:12:25,510 --> 00:12:27,060
If it's an inconvenience, never mind.

177
00:12:27,060 --> 00:12:28,150
That's not what I mean.

178
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:29,990
But to be honest, Mr. Zhang,

179
00:12:29,990 --> 00:12:31,420
I've never been to Hepu myself.

180
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:34,060
As a pearl diver, I wasn't allowed
to leave the pearl farm.

181
00:12:35,420 --> 00:12:37,060
You've never left the pearl farm?

182
00:12:41,150 --> 00:12:41,870
Well, in that case,

183
00:12:42,820 --> 00:12:45,270
why don't you
show me around the pearl farm instead?

184
00:12:45,270 --> 00:12:46,700
Already getting cozy, those two.

185
00:12:48,700 --> 00:12:50,350
Are you happy about winning the bet?

186
00:12:50,990 --> 00:12:51,910
Of course.

187
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:53,270
Now I can finally leave the pearl farm.

188
00:12:53,270 --> 00:12:54,580
So, what are your plans for the future?

189
00:12:56,300 --> 00:12:59,420
I plan to take a close friend with me,
leave Hepu,

190
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:00,870
and sell goods while traveling.

191
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:03,540
Just a small-time peddler?

192
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:05,420
No, a free and unrestrained

193
00:13:05,820 --> 00:13:06,870
grand merchant.

194
00:13:09,990 --> 00:13:12,270
Will Steward Cui give you a hard time?

195
00:13:13,300 --> 00:13:14,420
I'll be careful.

196
00:13:19,270 --> 00:13:20,820
By the way, Mr. Zhang,

197
00:13:21,460 --> 00:13:22,940
where are you from?

198
00:13:22,940 --> 00:13:23,540
Me?

199
00:13:24,910 --> 00:13:25,870
Chang'an.

200
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:27,750
The faraway Chang'an?

201
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,060
Three thousand li

202
00:13:29,060 --> 00:13:29,910
from here.

203
00:13:30,420 --> 00:13:31,750
What's it like in Chang'an?

204
00:13:32,420 --> 00:13:34,060
You've asked the right person.

205
00:13:34,870 --> 00:13:36,110
In Banzheng Ward,

206
00:13:36,110 --> 00:13:38,150
shops are filled
with countless books and ancient texts.

207
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:39,540
And in Fuxing Ward,

208
00:13:39,540 --> 00:13:41,350
you'll find the best-baked flatbread.

209
00:13:41,350 --> 00:13:42,300
Baked flatbread?

210
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:44,780
If you ever go to Chang'an,

211
00:13:45,030 --> 00:13:46,780
you must try
the water basin mutton there.

212
00:13:47,820 --> 00:13:49,300
In the West Market, you'll see Hu people

213
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:51,300
with high noses and deep-set eyes,

214
00:13:51,990 --> 00:13:53,420
and Hu women are all skilled
at singing and dancing.

215
00:13:54,180 --> 00:13:54,780
Oh,

216
00:13:55,110 --> 00:13:56,630
there's also this local custom.

217
00:13:56,630 --> 00:13:58,810
We write our wishes on a wooden plaque

218
00:13:59,110 --> 00:14:01,510
and hang it on a blessing tree.
This way, the wishes will come true.

219
00:14:01,510 --> 00:14:03,420
What does a blessing tree look like?

220
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:07,990
Unfortunately, there isn't one here.

221
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:09,630
Of course not.

222
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:12,990
No worries.

223
00:14:13,870 --> 00:14:15,030
Sincerity is all that matters.

224
00:14:15,030 --> 00:14:15,700
How about

225
00:14:16,820 --> 00:14:17,910
we use this tree right here?

226
00:14:21,990 --> 00:14:23,910
Come on. What's your wish?

227
00:14:36,630 --> 00:14:37,510
Freedom.

228
00:14:39,580 --> 00:14:40,750
I want freedom.

229
00:14:45,150 --> 00:14:45,820
Alright.

230
00:15:04,870 --> 00:15:05,630
"Freedom."

231
00:15:11,150 --> 00:15:12,060
Is that all?

232
00:15:12,060 --> 00:15:13,030
Make your wish first.

233
00:15:13,420 --> 00:15:14,660
Then I'll put
the plaque up there for you.

234
00:15:30,780 --> 00:15:31,940
Thank you, Mr. Zhang.

235
00:15:36,930 --> 00:15:39,940
[Freedom]

236
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:42,270
May your heart stay
as clear as a mirror,

237
00:15:43,180 --> 00:15:44,420
and may all your wishes come true.

238
00:15:59,660 --> 00:16:00,540
Steward Cui.

239
00:16:02,700 --> 00:16:03,700
Master Yan?

240
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:12,630
What brings you here so late at night?

241
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:15,420
I'm here for my 15-millimeter pearls,
of course.

242
00:16:17,060 --> 00:16:17,870
You may go.

243
00:16:17,870 --> 00:16:18,630
Yes, sir.

244
00:16:25,270 --> 00:16:26,270
The goods are ready.

245
00:16:26,510 --> 00:16:28,660
But didn't we agree
to complete the deal tomorrow?

246
00:16:29,110 --> 00:16:30,300
I need to leave tonight.

247
00:16:30,940 --> 00:16:31,820
So,

248
00:16:32,580 --> 00:16:33,820
let's settle it now.

249
00:16:33,820 --> 00:16:35,510
Why the sudden rush?

250
00:16:40,300 --> 00:16:41,820
Steward Cui, don't play dumb.

251
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:44,460
Gold willow leaves aren't something
ordinary folks can possess.

252
00:16:44,460 --> 00:16:45,580
You should know that.

253
00:16:45,580 --> 00:16:47,060
Otherwise, you wouldn't

254
00:16:47,060 --> 00:16:49,390
still be here at this hour,
waiting for news.

255
00:16:51,150 --> 00:16:52,540
I can also tell you

256
00:16:52,910 --> 00:16:55,630
that Prince Ying's sworn brother left
the capital and headed south recently.

257
00:16:56,180 --> 00:16:58,810
Although he's just
a scholar at Xiuwen Pavilion,

258
00:16:59,030 --> 00:17:00,910
it's said he's highly trusted
by both Prince Ying

259
00:17:01,270 --> 00:17:03,180
and the Emperor.

260
00:17:03,510 --> 00:17:04,270
What's more,

261
00:17:05,390 --> 00:17:06,470
his surname is Zhang.

262
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:09,910
Is he the man from today's...?

263
00:17:10,940 --> 00:17:12,300
I didn't say anything.

264
00:17:12,700 --> 00:17:14,300
I'm just a businessman.

265
00:17:14,910 --> 00:17:18,270
To me, what matters most
are money and safety.

266
00:17:18,270 --> 00:17:19,910
But you brought him here.

267
00:17:20,630 --> 00:17:22,270
What are you talking about?

268
00:17:22,270 --> 00:17:23,660
Mr. Peng was on that ship too.

269
00:17:23,660 --> 00:17:25,300
I only found out
about this myself recently.

270
00:17:25,630 --> 00:17:26,700
I've also heard

271
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:28,630
that Prince Ying

272
00:17:29,630 --> 00:17:32,300
and Prince Tan
are in fierce conflict these days.

273
00:17:32,300 --> 00:17:34,510
Your family has always
served Prince Tan, hasn't it?

